        <li><a href="foundation-border.html" class="foundation-link">Border</a></li>
        <li><a href="foundation-radius.html" class="foundation-link">Radius</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>

    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Elevation</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Use elevation to define surface hierarchy, guide attention, and communicate interaction across Endpoint Central workflows.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

          <div class="doc-section" id="overview">
            <p>In Prism, elevation represents layered surfaces that form the foundation of the UI. These layers create the structure where content, actions, and interactions live.</p>
            <p>A strong elevation system improves clarity, focus, and usability across dense enterprise interfaces.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="principles">
            <h2>Elevation principles</h2>

            <h3>1. Use elevation to show hierarchy</h3>
            <p>Elevation defines which surface is base, interactive, floating, or blocking.</p>
            <p><strong>Rule:</strong> Higher elevation = higher priority.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>page background → lowest</li>
              <li>cards → medium</li>
              <li>dropdown → high</li>
              <li>modal → highest</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2. Use elevation sparingly</h3>
            <p>Too many elevation levels create visual noise.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>limit to defined elevation steps</li>
              <li>avoid stacking multiple shadows</li>
              <li>do not combine heavy borders + shadows</li>
              <li>use spacing before adding elevation</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="doc-callout">Whitespace first → elevation second.</div>

            <h3>3. Elevation must be consistent</h3>
            <p>The same interaction should always use the same elevation level.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>all dropdowns → same elevation</li>
              <li>all modals → same elevation</li>
              <li>all tooltips → same elevation</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Inconsistent elevation breaks user expectation.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="layers">
            <h2>Elevation layers</h2>
            <p>Prism defines a structured elevation scale.</p>

            <div class="elev-grid">
              <div class="elev-tile elev-sunken"><div class="elev-tile-name">sunken</div><div class="elev-tile-use">inputs, embedded panels</div></div>
              <div class="elev-tile elev-default"><div class="elev-tile-name">default</div><div class="elev-tile-use">base page, tables</div></div>
              <div class="elev-tile elev-raised"><div class="elev-tile-name">raised</div><div class="elev-tile-use">cards, widgets</div></div>
              <div class="elev-tile elev-overlay"><div class="elev-tile-name">overlay</div><div class="elev-tile-use">dropdowns, popovers</div></div>
              <div class="elev-tile elev-modal"><div class="elev-tile-name">modal</div><div class="elev-tile-use">dialogs, blocking layers</div></div>
            </div>

            <table class="doc-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>elevation.surface.sunken</code></td><td>input fields, embedded panels</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>elevation.surface.default</code></td><td>base page, tables</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>elevation.surface.raised</code></td><td>cards, widgets</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>elevation.surface.overlay</code></td><td>dropdowns, popovers</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>elevation.surface.modal</code></td><td>dialogs, blocking layers</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="shadow-system">
            <h2>Shadow system</h2>
            <p>Elevation is visually represented using shadows and surface contrast.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>use tokenized shadow values only</li>
              <li>avoid custom shadows</li>
              <li>combine shadow + background contrast</li>
              <li>ensure shadows work in dark mode</li>
              <li>avoid heavy blur shadows in dense tables</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="patterns">
            <h2>Endpoint-specific elevation patterns</h2>

            <h3>Device inventory</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>base table → <strong>default</strong> surface</li>
              <li>selected row actions → <strong>raised</strong> surface</li>
              <li>inline editors → <strong>overlay</strong></li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Inspector panel</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>main content → <strong>default</strong></li>
              <li>inspector rail → <strong>raised</strong></li>
              <li>nested sections → subtle elevation only</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Patch deployment</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>step container → <strong>raised</strong></li>
              <li>dropdown selection → <strong>overlay</strong></li>
              <li>confirmation modal → <strong>modal</strong> elevation</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Security workflows</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>dashboard widgets → <strong>raised</strong></li>
              <li>threat detail popover → <strong>overlay</strong></li>
              <li>isolation confirmation → <strong>modal</strong></li>
            </ul>

            <h3>AI insights</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>suggestion cards → <strong>raised</strong></li>
              <li>explanation popovers → <strong>overlay</strong></li>
              <li>action preview → <strong>overlay</strong> or <strong>modal</strong> based on risk</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="interaction">
            <h2>Elevation + interaction</h2>
            <h4>Hover</h4>
            <ul><li>slight elevation increase</li><li>subtle shadow only</li></ul>
            <h4>Active / pressed</h4>
            <ul><li>reduce elevation</li><li>simulate "pressed surface"</li></ul>
            <h4>Focus</h4>
            <ul><li>do not rely on elevation</li><li>use border + focus ring instead</li></ul>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="grid-spacing">
            <h2>Elevation + grid and spacing</h2>
            <p>Elevation should not replace layout structure.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>use grid for layout</li>
              <li>use spacing for grouping</li>
              <li>use elevation only for layering</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="dodont-grid">
              <div class="dodont-card dont">
                <div class="dodont-label">DON'T</div>
                <p>Using shadows to separate sections.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="dodont-card do">
                <div class="dodont-label">DO</div>
                <p>Spacing + grid define layout; elevation defines interaction depth.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="accessibility">
            <h2>Accessibility</h2>
            <p>Elevation must remain perceivable for all users.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>never rely on shadow alone</li>
              <li>pair elevation with border, contrast, background shift</li>
              <li>ensure visibility in dark mode</li>
              <li>maintain clear focus states</li>
              <li>support reduced motion environments</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="anti-patterns">
            <h2>Anti-patterns</h2>
            <p>Avoid these common enterprise mistakes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>too many shadow levels</li>
              <li>heavy drop shadows on tables</li>
              <li>inconsistent modal elevation</li>
              <li>nested cards with identical elevation</li>
              <li>using elevation instead of spacing</li>
              <li>invisible shadows in dark mode</li>
              <li>mixing blur styles across modules</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="doc-section" id="principle">
            <h2>Principle</h2>
            <p>In Prism, elevation creates spatial clarity.</p>
            <p>The right elevation system helps Endpoint Central users understand structure, focus on what matters, and confidently interact across complex layered workflows.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="feedback-banner" style="display: none;">
            <div>
              <div class="fb-text">Help us improve this page</div>
              <div class="fb-sub">Share your feedback to help shape the Elevation documentation.</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px;">
              <button class="feedback-btn primary" onclick="window.open('https://cliq.zoho.in/company/60002085329/channels/prismdesignsystembyuemssupportfeedback','_blank')">Give Feedback</button>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <aside class="toc-sidebar">
          <h4 class="toc-heading">On this page</h4>
          <ul class="toc-nav" id="toc-nav"></ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>

  <script>
// Sidebar search: filter foundation nav links by query
    const sidebarSearchInput = document.querySelector('.sidebar-search input');
    const foundationNavItems = document.querySelectorAll('.foundation-nav li');
    if (sidebarSearchInput && foundationNavItems.length) {
      sidebarSearchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
        const q = e.target.value.trim().toLowerCase();
        foundationNavItems.forEach(li => {
          const text = li.textContent.trim().toLowerCase();
          li.style.display = !q || text.includes(q) ? '' : 'none';
        });
      });
      document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
        if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === 'k') {
          e.preventDefault();
          sidebarSearchInput.focus();
        }
        if (e.key === 'Escape' && document.activeElement === sidebarSearchInput) {
          sidebarSearchInput.value = '';
          sidebarSearchInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
          sidebarSearchInput.blur();
        }
      });
    }

    const themeToggle = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
    const moonIcon = document.getElementById('moonIcon');
    const sunIcon = document.getElementById('sunIcon');
    const currentTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
    if (currentTheme === 'dark') {
      document.documentElement.removeAttribute('data-theme');
      moonIcon.style.display = 'block'; sunIcon.style.display = 'none';
    }
    themeToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
      let theme = document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme');
      if (theme === 'light') {
        document.documentElement.removeAttribute('data-theme');
        localStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');
        moonIcon.style.display = 'block'; sunIcon.style.display = 'none';
      } else {
        document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', 'light');
        localStorage.setItem('theme', 'light');
        moonIcon.style.display = 'none'; sunIcon.style.display = 'block';
      }
    });

    // Build TOC from h2 headings
    (function() {
      const tocList = document.getElementById('toc-nav');
      if (!tocList) return;
      const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.main-content-inner h2');
      sections.forEach(h => {
        const section = h.closest('.doc-section');
        if (!section || !section.id) return;
        const li = document.createElement('li');
        const a = document.createElement('a');
        a.className = 'toc-link';
        a.href = '#' + section.id;
        a.textContent = h.textContent;
        li.appendChild(a);
        tocList.appendChild(li);
      });
    })();
  </script>
<script>
(function(){
  const nav = document.querySelector('.nav');
  if (!nav) return;
  const toggle = () => {
    if (window.scrollY > 10) nav.classList.add('scrolled');
    else nav.classList.remove('scrolled');
  };
  toggle();
  window.addEventListener('scroll', toggle, { passive: true });
})();
</script>
<script>
(function(){
  const hamburger = document.querySelector('.nav-hamburger');
  const sidebar = document.querySelector('.sidebar');
  const backdrop = document.querySelector('.sidebar-backdrop');
  const navLinks = document.querySelector('.nav-links');
  if (!hamburger || !sidebar || !backdrop) return;

  // Build a mobile-only nav section at the top of the sidebar by cloning the nav links
  if (navLinks && !sidebar.querySelector('.sidebar-mobile-nav')) {
    const mobileNav = document.createElement('div');
    mobileNav.className = 'sidebar-mobile-nav';
    const heading = document.createElement('h4');
    heading.textContent = 'Navigate';
    mobileNav.appendChild(heading);
    const ul = document.createElement('ul');
    navLinks.querySelectorAll(':scope > a').forEach(a => {
      const li = document.createElement('li');
      const clone = a.cloneNode(true);
      li.appendChild(clone);
      ul.appendChild(li);
    });
    navLinks.querySelectorAll(':scope > .nav-dropdown > .nav-dropdown-menu > a').forEach(a => {
      const li = document.createElement('li');
      const clone = a.cloneNode(true);
      li.appendChild(clone);
      ul.appendChild(li);
    });
    mobileNav.appendChild(ul);
    sidebar.insertBefore(mobileNav, sidebar.firstChild);
  }

  const open = () => {
    sidebar.classList.add('open');
    backdrop.classList.add('open');
    document.body.classList.add('sidebar-locked');
    hamburger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
  };
  const close = () => {
    sidebar.classList.remove('open');
    backdrop.classList.remove('open');
    document.body.classList.remove('sidebar-locked');
    hamburger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
  };
  hamburger.addEventListener('click', () => sidebar.classList.contains('open') ? close() : open());
  backdrop.addEventListener('click', close);
  document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => { if (e.key === 'Escape' && sidebar.classList.contains('open')) close(); });
  sidebar.addEventListener('click', (e) => { if (e.target.closest('a')) close(); });
})();
</script>

